of their temporary ongoing need. What sort of information do you think we could provide that would</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> distinguish between </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">what was </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">a rati</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">onal decision by a borrower to take a rollover, and what was a sign that someone is in really serious</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> debt problems?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14.2pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Richard Lloyd</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">: That would be a more credible assertion for them to make if they were doing proper</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> affordability checks at the outset</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">. From our survey</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">—</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">we</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> have all done a lot of surveys on this</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">—</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">h</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">alf the people </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">that we have surveyed who have taken out</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">payday loans said that they have taken out credit that they could not afford to repay. Now, i</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">f they are not carrying out proper affordability checks, you have </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">got </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">to </span><s