st important</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">Actually, the issue about whether or not the industry wanted to review their compliance might not have mattered had</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> we found</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">, when we tested it, </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">that </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">the customers were saying that there was compliance</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">. But the combination of a</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> lack of interest in charting whether that code had been complied with and the fact that customers were then reporting significant problems certainly suggests, very strongly, that the industry was not taking it anything like as seriously as it should have been</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> in general terms.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">Q145 </span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Ann McKechin:</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> I have a</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> couple of questions for Mr Fisher</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">You</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> have the power to revoke licenc</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">es in extreme cases</span><span style="font